      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Nationalism is a double-edged sword that can either foster unity or incite conflict depending on how it is defined and practiced. While it can provide a sense of identity and social cohesion, it often leads to xenophobia and the suppression of minority rights when it becomes exclusionary. A country can function without strict nationalism by relying on civic nationalism, which emphasizes shared values and laws over ethnic or cultural homogeneity. Ultimately, the danger lies in prioritizing national interests above human rights, which has historically driven wars and oppression.",
